This dusty Datapad seems to contain the journal of a prospective Sith Archaeologist that had ventured here centuries ago. The majority of the journal is composed of rather uninteresting notes regarding the architecture of Tulak Hords tomb, but the last entry catches your attention...

"These ancient terminals appear to control the door mechanism currently blocking off the adjacent chamber. They are old...very old, holding age beyond comprehension, yet I've managed to decode it's operating sequence, and the door is no longer an issue. The runes carved on the walls nearby roughly translate into a warning..the next chamber may be trapped. I'll have to proceed with caution."
Loosely nailed, this wooden crate appears intended for temporary storage.
